Xunyuan Sun & Jing Du

library(DataComputing)
library(mosaic)

Guiding Question

Demographic changes in 15 and 17 years

Become acquainted with the data sources

  1. Where did you find them? We found these data sources from kaggle.

  2. Who collected/maintains them? The user name is MuonNeutrino

  3. When & Why were they originally collected? These data sources was updated one years ago.

  4. What does a case represent in each data source, and how many total cases are available? In acs2015_census_tract_data, each case for 2015 means each census tract in the U.S. In acs2017_census_tract_data, each case for 2017 means each census tract in the U.S.

  5. What are some of the variables that you plan to use TractId, State, County, TotalPop, Men, Women, Hispanic, White, Black, Native, Asian, Pacific, Income

rr Census_Tract_2015 <- read.csv(://raw.githubusercontent.com/XYSunPSU/Final-Project/master/acs2015_census_tract_data.csv, header = T)

Census_Tract_2017 <- read.csv(://raw.githubusercontent.com/XYSunPSU/Final-Project/master/acs2017_census_tract_data.csv, header = T)

rr Census_Tract_2015

rr Census_Tract_2017

Explore intuition related to research question

  1. Create some informative plots and summary statistics

rr graphdata <- Census_Tract_2015%>% filter(State == )

ggplot(data=graphdata,aes(x=County,y=TotalPop ))+geom_bar(stat=‘identity’,position=‘stack’, width=.9)
